 Pak speedster set to join IPL
Lahore: Shoaib Akhtar is set to play in the BCCI-organised IPL next year, saying he has sought permission from the authorities. I have been approached by the IPL and I have applied for permission from the Pakistan Cricket Board to sign the contract, Shoaib said on Saturday. I have always liked the Indian crowd and love to play in India. Hopefully I will be in the Pakistan squad for the next months tour there and will get to play in the league. Sources close to Shoaib have said he has been offered $300,000 to play in IPL. (AGENCIES) 
